        <div class="disclaimer-img"><i class="fa fa-exclamation-circle"></i></div>
        <div class="disclaimer-text"><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> This calculator provides an APR estimate by first calculating the effective annual rate based on compounding and then using a simple version of the APR formula: APR = (Total Interest Over the Term + Loan Fees)/Loan Amount x (12/Loan Term in Months)</div>
